                          imgCredit:'jeffreyw, CC BY 2.0',
                          name:'Ruby-throated hummingbird',latin:'Archilochus colubris',era:'Miocene',
                          desc:'A migratory hummingbird that winters in Central America and breeds across eastern North America. The most common hummingbird in eastern North America, with a population of about 35 million.',
                          detail:'Males sport an iridescent ruby-red throat gorget that appears black in low light. These tiny birds can fly non-stop across the Gulf of Mexico — an 800 km journey over open water — during migration, visiting hundreds of flowers daily.',
