                      name:'Cetaceans',latin:'Order Cetacea',era:'~50 Mya',
                      desc:'Whales, dolphins, and porpoises — fully aquatic mammals descended from terrestrial artiodactyls related to hippos. The transition from land to sea occurred ~50 Mya, documented by transitional fossils like Pakicetus.',
