                        name:'Bottlenose dolphin',latin:'Tursiops truncatus',era:'Neogene',
                        desc:'One of the most widely recognized dolphin species, found in temperate and tropical oceans worldwide. Known for its intelligence, social behavior, and characteristic curved mouth that resembles a smile.',
                        detail:'Bottlenose dolphins use sophisticated echolocation producing clicks at frequencies up to 130 kHz. They demonstrate self-awareness in mirror tests, use tools like sponges to protect their rostrums while foraging, and maintain complex social alliances spanning decades.',
