                        name:'Humpback whale',latin:'Megaptera novaeangliae',era:'Neogene',
                        desc:'A 25-tonne acrobat that breaches entirely out of the water. Males produce the most complex songs in the animal kingdom — compositions lasting up to 20 minutes that evolve culturally across ocean basins.',
                        detail:'Humpback whale songs spread like pop hits across the Pacific. New compositions originate in Australia and sweep eastward. They also use "bubble net feeding" — blowing spiral curtains of bubbles to herd fish.',
