                        name:'Sperm whale',latin:'Physeter macrocephalus',era:'Neogene',
                        desc:'Has the largest brain of any animal ever — 8 kg. The loudest animal on Earth at 230 dB. Dives to 2,250 m for over an hour to hunt giant squid in total darkness using the most powerful sonar in nature.',
                        detail:'Sperm whale social groups use distinct click patterns called codas — essentially dialects — that identify their clan. Different clans share the same ocean but rarely interact, creating cultural boundaries.',
                        funFact:'Sperm whales have the largest brain ever (8 kg), produce the loudest sound of any animal (230 dB), and dive deeper than any other mammal to fight giant squid.',
