                          name:'Great Apes',latin:'Family Hominidae',era:'~20 Mya',
                          desc:'The family that includes orangutans, gorillas, chimpanzees, bonobos, and humans. All great apes are characterised by large brains, no tail, an upright posture, and complex social structures. We share a common ancestor who lived roughly 20 million years ago.',
