                              desc:'The most solitary of the great apes and the only primarily arboreal one. Orangutans in Borneo and Sumatra have distinct cultures — some populations use tools to extract honey while others never do. They have the longest birth interval of any mammal.',
                              detail:'An orangutan mother nurses her offspring for up to 8 years — longer than any other mammal. They construct elaborate sleeping nests each night and have been observed using leaves as rain hats.',
