                    name:'Phytophthora infestans',latin:'Phytophthora infestans',era:'Modern',
                    desc:'The water mold that caused the Irish Potato Famine of 1845–1852, killing approximately one million people. Despite resembling a fungus, it belongs to the Stramenopiles — relatives of brown algae.',
                    detail:'P. infestans spreads with terrifying speed in cool wet conditions — a single lesion releases thousands of sporangia per hour. Modern potato crops still require intensive fungicide treatment.',
